%N A396563 Array read by ascending antidiagonals: A(n, k) is the determinant of the k X k matrix, where the (i, j)-th entry is |Stirling1(n + i + 2, n + j)|.
%H A396563 Wikipedia, <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Falling_and_rising_factorials">Falling and rising factorials</a>
%F A396563 Conjecture: B(n, k, m) = (Sum_{j_1=0..n} Sum_{j_2=0..j_1} ... Sum_{j_m=0..j_{m-1}} (-1)^(j_1 + j_2 + ... + j_m) * (Product_{1 <= q < p <= m} (j_q - j_p + p - q)^2) * Product_{t=1..m} (n+t-1)_{j_t} * (n-j_t+t)^(n+k) / (j_t+m-t)!) / (Product_{i=0..m-1} (n+i)!) where B(n, k, m) is the determinant of the k X k matrix with (i, j)-th entry is |Stirling1(n+m+i, n+j)|, where (x)_{n} is the falling factorial defined as (x)_{n} = Product_{k=0..n-1} (x-k).
%e A396563 Array starts:
